    "title": "Integrative Close",
    "objective": "Synthesize the relationship between a specific generation source and the standard UK transmission voltages.",
    "retrievalTextLines": [
      "We have established that electricity generation is the starting point of the supply chain, utilizing a variety of sources from fossil fuels to renewables like biomass and wind.",
      "Once generated, this power must enter the transmission 'motorway' to be moved efficiently over long distances.",
      "To minimize energy loss during this journey, the voltage is stepped up to one of the three specific UK transmission ratings before it ever reaches the local distribution network."
    ],
    "questionText": "A new large-scale biomass power plant is being commissioned to supply electricity to a city several hundred miles away. Explain how this specific generation method fits into the UK supply chain and identify the three precise high-voltage levels it will enter to be transmitted across the national grid.",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "The learner must identify biomass as a generation method (specifically a renewable or organic-based source).",
      "The learner must correctly list the three UK transmission voltages: 400 kV, 275 kV, and 132 kV.",
      "The response should link the generation source to the transmission network as the 'bulk movement' or 'long-distance' phase of the supply chain."
    ],
    "hint": "Recall the 'Big Three' voltages used for the UK's high-voltage transmission network and ensure you include the specific kV units."
  }
}

